16 SECTION 2. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 454 IS CREATED TO
17 READ AS FOLLOWS:
18 (1) If a civil action is filed and the defendant to the action believes that it is an
19 abusive civil action, the claim may be raised by the defendant by petitioning the
20 court to restrict abusive litigation:
21 (a) In the answer to the civil action; or
22 (b) By motion made at any time during the civil action.
23 (2) The court may, on its own motion, conduct a hearing pursuant to Section 3 of
24 this Act to determine whether the civil action is an abusive civil action.
25 (3) The Administrative Office of the Courts shall establish a form application to be
26 used in filing a petition for an order restricting abusive litigation.
